<TITLE> Rajshahi division to get 6 new sub-stations </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 13 (bdnews24.com)The government has approved a proposal to set up six power sub-stations in six districts of Rajshahi division, joint secretary of the cabinet division Nurul Karim said on Tuesday. The sub-stations will be established at Rangpur, Gaibandha, Sirajganj, Pabna, Dinajpur and Thakurgaon with 33KV capacity, Karim said after a meeting of the cabinet committee on public purchase. The project will be funded with almost Tk 5 crore by the government and foreign aid of 8.3 million euros. The committee also approved three other proposals, including one to import 200,000 metric tonnes of urea at a cost of Tk 414 crore. Moreover, premium on fuel was also restructured, Karim said. Premium on diesel was set to $5.75 from $5.90 and to $6.40 from $6.60 for kerosene for the period of Sept-Dec this year. For the months of Jan-June 2010 premium on diesel will be $4.70 and $6.25 on kerosene. The committee also approved the proposal to buy 1.4 million metric tonnes of petroleum withfrom Petronas Trading of Malaysia newly fixed premium. bdn
